110
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:22,680
No, it's fine.

111
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,800
Go on, speak.

112
00:05:24,079 --> 00:05:25,879
Let me briefly explain to you.

113
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,680
Simply put,

114
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:30,040
we provide the capital...

115
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:31,480
and obtain Peng Le Xuan's...

116
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,680
brand rights and management control.

117
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,199
Then we give it a complete makeover.

118
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:38,360
First, we renovate Peng Le Xuan.

119
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,959
Then, combining internet...

120
00:05:39,959 --> 00:05:41,439
marketing concepts,

121
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:44,240
we create a new-concept roast duck...

122
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:46,199
that blends tradition and modernity.

123
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:47,639
Strive to make our Peng Le Xuan...

124
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:48,839
bigger and stronger.

125
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,959
My little shop? Is it up to it?

126
00:05:57,439 --> 00:05:59,319
Don't underestimate our Peng Le Xuan.

127
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,319
Here's the thing.

128
00:06:02,439 --> 00:06:03,439
Let me show you...

129
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:04,800
the proposal I've prepared.

130
00:06:18,199 --> 00:06:19,680
Young Mistress, you're here for candied haws.

131
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,240
Yes.

132
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,399
Please pick a skewered one.

133
00:06:21,399 --> 00:06:22,319
I'll take one of these.

134
00:06:23,319 --> 00:06:25,279
Thank you for your patronage. Please take care.

135
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:26,319
Come in and have a taste.

136
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,360
Alright, I'll definitely come another day.

137
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,720
How about a pottery figurine?

138
00:06:32,279 --> 00:06:33,279
Boss Ma.

139
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,319
My respects to you.

140
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:37,120
Congratulations!

141
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,079
Congratulations to you as well.

142
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:39,480
Excellent.

143
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,639
Thank you, thank you.

144
00:06:41,319 --> 00:06:42,120
Come by another day.

145
00:06:42,399 --> 00:06:43,279
Yes, yes.

146
00:06:44,519 --> 00:06:46,519
Now, in the capital city,

147
00:06:46,519 --> 00:06:48,560
roast duck is all the rage.

148
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:51,720
Among the most exquisite feasts,

149
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,319
Peng Le Xuan stands alone.

150
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:58,439
Its master, Ma Hezhen, excels at crafting delicacies.

151
00:06:58,439 --> 00:06:59,759
Those who catch its aroma

152
00:06:59,759 --> 00:07:03,000
from ten paces away are all drawn in, mouths watering.

153
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,000
Sweet but not cloying,

154
00:07:20,199 --> 00:07:21,680
salty but not overpowering,

155
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,160
mild but not bland,

156
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,720
rich but not greasy.

157
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:29,399
Patrons chatter excitedly,

158
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,480
as if enchanted, they dance,

159
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:34,600
often wishing to devour the very dishware.

160
00:07:45,959 --> 00:07:47,959
The Empress Dowager heard of his fame

161
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:48,879
and summoned him.

162
00:07:50,639 --> 00:07:51,959
He replied,

163
00:07:51,959 --> 00:07:54,160
"Cooking is like practicing medicine.

164
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:57,360
With a focused mind, I diagnose the suitability of all ingredients,

165
00:07:57,360 --> 00:08:00,319
and carefully balance the fire and water.

166
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:03,199
Thus, ten thousand mouths find sweetness as one."

167
00:08:03,199 --> 00:08:05,759
The Empress Dowager was pleased and rewarded him,

168
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,759
then ordered him to provide meals for the military camp.

169
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:11,519
He was granted the title "Culinary Captain".

170
00:08:11,519 --> 00:08:13,839
His descendants inherited it.

171
00:08:15,399 --> 00:08:17,519
I just heard you mention "comeuppance", right?

172
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,120
Are you all very knowledgeable about business wars?

173
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:19,920
Of course.

174
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,759
Then have you ever seen a real business war?

175
00:08:22,439 --> 00:08:23,720
The Century Truth War.

176
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,279
Marvelous Company versus Wall Street.

177
00:08:25,279 --> 00:08:26,639
Blackwater shorting Libaid.

178
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:28,160
Nokela taking on AP one-on-one.

179
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,240
Have you heard of all these?

180
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,120
Of course.

181
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,679
Sorry, I made all of those up.

182
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,200
And how should a CEO date?

183
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,000
Tell us.

184
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,679
How do you write a "smoldering gaze"?

185
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,879
Have you been to a bookstore, seen the bestseller list?

186
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,480
Are you sure this is the mainstream?

187
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,639
And have you asked people

188
00:08:44,639 --> 00:08:45,919
if they really want to watch this kind of thing?

189
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,679
Do they genuinely like it,

190
00:08:47,679 --> 00:08:48,639
or do they just have no other choice?

191
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,120
You see,

192
00:08:50,519 --> 00:08:51,440
your train of thought

193
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,879
sounds completely unrealistic from the get-go.

194
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,320
Our requirements for script review are very strict.

195
00:08:55,519 --> 00:08:56,840
And this isn't our standard

196
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:57,919
script review process.

197
00:08:58,279 --> 00:08:59,320
Alright, alright, alright.

198
00:08:59,399 --> 00:09:01,159
Let's humbly listen to

199
00:09:01,159 --> 00:09:03,320
the feedback they're giving on the script.

200
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,039
Um, what's your boss's name?

201
00:09:15,759 --> 00:09:17,240
Tang Zhen, from the Copyright Department.

202
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,840
Is that Sarah still your secretary?

203
00:09:22,279 --> 00:09:23,320
I haven't returned to the country.

204
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:24,960
Here's the thing.

205
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,240
My uncle is currently at your place in a script meeting.

206
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,159
He didn't bring any tea.

207
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:29,879
Can you have Sarah bring some down?

208
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,759
She seems to be an intern.

209
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,039
Not a supervisor.

210
00:09:35,279 --> 00:09:36,960
She can't make decisions on matters like this.

211
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:37,919
Tong Daxi.

212
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,039
An old man.

213
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,360
Xiao Ma.

214
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:41,000
No, no, no.

215
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:42,879
Don't you come down to deliver it.

216
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:44,519
The old man doesn't like such a high-profile gesture.

217
00:09:46,879 --> 00:09:47,559
Alright then.

218
00:09:48,399 --> 00:09:49,759
I owe you one.

219
00:09:50,519 --> 00:09:52,639
Good, I'll send you two more boxes in a couple of days.

220
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,399
This time, make it last.

221
00:09:54,399 --> 00:09:55,759
It's a nutritional supplement, not a meal.

222
00:09:56,799 --> 00:09:58,519
Don't ask so many questions. That's it.

223
00:10:01,799 --> 00:10:03,279
Yes, yes, Brother Zhen.

224
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,559
No, you don't know him.

225
00:10:19,799 --> 00:10:20,519
Hello?

226
00:10:21,679 --> 00:10:22,440
Brother Zhen.

227
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,960
Qiao... Vice President Qiao told you?

228
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:30,000
Who is Vice President Qiao?

229
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,200
He's the one in charge of

230
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:34,799
their entire audiovisual division, the vice president.

231
00:10:35,799 --> 00:10:36,279
Yes.

232
00:10:36,279 --> 00:10:36,840
Um,

233
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,000
I just call him Xiao Qiao.

234
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,399
He's my classmate from the CEO training course.

235
00:10:44,559 --> 00:10:46,080
Teacher Tong, sorry about that.

236
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,000
Please wait a moment.

237
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,759
Our boss,

238
00:10:47,759 --> 00:10:49,639
Brother Zhen will see you right away.

239
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,279
Thank you, thank you.

240
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,320
Thanks.

241
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:54,080
Mr. Ma, sorry about earlier.

242
00:10:54,519 --> 00:10:55,240
It's fine.

243
00:10:58,519 --> 00:11:00,519
Teacher Tong, I'll make you some tea.

244
00:11:00,519 --> 00:11:01,360
Would you like black tea,

245
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:01,799
Thank you, thank you.

246
00:11:01,799 --> 00:11:02,799
or green tea, or...

247
00:11:02,799 --> 00:11:04,200
No, no, don't trouble yourself.

248
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:05,919
Teacher Tong,

249
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,039
some water?

250
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,399
I'm not thirsty right now.

251
00:11:09,399 --> 00:11:09,799
Really, I won't drink.

252
00:11:09,799 --> 00:11:10,480
Not thirsty.

253
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,399
Not thirsty.

254
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:12,679
So you see,

255
00:11:12,759 --> 00:11:14,519
this century-old cultural heritage,

256
00:11:14,519 --> 00:11:16,960
just the signboard of our Peng Le Xuan,

257
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,440
offers limitless possibilities.

258
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:21,279
This is what capital values most.

259
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,559
Let me tell you,

260
00:11:22,919 --> 00:11:25,480
