558
00:22:25,160 --> 00:22:27,599
Dong Qian's idea is not wrong.

559
00:22:27,599 --> 00:22:28,759
The problem lies in

560
00:22:28,759 --> 00:22:30,440
her representing the interests of capital.

561
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:33,559
So we have to do this ourselves.

562
00:22:34,279 --> 00:22:36,759
Funding, distribution, customers, promotion...

563
00:22:36,759 --> 00:22:37,839
and so on.

564
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:40,720
Everything needed to start a restaurant business,

565
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,000
I have it all right here.

566
00:22:43,039 --> 00:22:44,799
All these years I've worked at the big company,

567
00:22:44,799 --> 00:22:47,039
were preparation for Peng Le Xuan's future.

568
00:22:47,039 --> 00:22:47,680
Second brother.

569
00:22:47,799 --> 00:22:50,599
I advise you, don't get this idea.

570
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,200
Why not?

571
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,599
Look.

572
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:55,880
If Qianqian does this,

573
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:58,799
she has capital backing her, investing money.

574
00:22:58,799 --> 00:22:59,400
Right?

575
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:02,599
If she loses, the capital doesn't care.

576
00:23:02,599 --> 00:23:03,920
Whether it makes or loses money,

577
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,880
that's what capital does, right?

578
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:08,480
It doesn't affect Qianqian's own income.

579
00:23:08,839 --> 00:23:09,559
Isn't that so?

580
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:11,440
But if you run this operation,

581
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:13,279
you... you're spending your own money.

582
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:14,880
Let's not even mention

583
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:17,359
how all those deals of yours over the years

584
00:23:17,359 --> 00:23:18,279
got started.

585
00:23:18,279 --> 00:23:19,160
I know all about it.

586
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:21,680
That money was hard-earned and put in your pocket.

587
00:23:21,839 --> 00:23:23,880
I can't let you take this risk.

588
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:26,160
Big brother, that's easy to solve.

589
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,759
I can also go raise funds.

590
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,039
Isn't financing the same?

591
00:23:30,039 --> 00:23:31,880
That money comes to you,

592
00:23:32,079 --> 00:23:32,799
but wouldn't you

593
00:23:32,799 --> 00:23:34,799
still be bound by personal liability?

594
00:23:34,799 --> 00:23:37,160
Wouldn't you have to sign a betting agreement?

595
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:40,039
You even understand these things?

596
00:23:40,039 --> 00:23:41,319
What don't I understand?

597
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:43,319
Five thousand years of history, past and present, domestic and foreign.

598
00:23:43,319 --> 00:23:45,759
Tell me, wouldn't you have to sign a bet?

599
00:23:46,359 --> 00:23:48,640
Big brother, everything you say is correct.

600
00:23:49,039 --> 00:23:50,640
But I'm not a novice.

601
00:23:50,799 --> 00:23:52,440
Back when I was in investment,

602
00:23:52,559 --> 00:23:53,559
those VPs today

603
00:23:53,559 --> 00:23:54,920
were still in diapers.

604
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:57,519
A whole crowd of people begged me for favors.

605
00:23:57,519 --> 00:23:58,599
Who dared to set conditions for me?

606
00:23:58,599 --> 00:23:59,799
No, no, no.

607
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:02,720
That was then, this is now.

608
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:03,319
No, big brother...

609
00:24:03,319 --> 00:24:05,720
Listen to me, don't get this idea.

610
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,400
Your big brother won't let you take this risk.

611
00:24:08,279 --> 00:24:09,000
Let's eat.

612
00:24:13,319 --> 00:24:14,640
This time,

613
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,640
I really should thank you properly.

614
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:17,759
Here.

615
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:18,920
Uncle Tong.

616
00:24:19,039 --> 00:24:19,640
No need.

617
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:21,200
Drink up.

618
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:22,200
Here.

619
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:25,039
Come on, uncle toasts you a cup.

620
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:26,759
Uncle Tong, listen to me.

621
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:30,319
You can't write this script.

622
00:24:31,759 --> 00:24:33,400
Why not?

623
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,079
I helped you this time,

624
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,960
but if you write this kind of script,

625
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,319
you'll be subject to gossip and criticism.

626
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,359
Are you willing to accept that?

627
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,759
Actually, I'm writing this script

628
00:24:47,759 --> 00:24:51,279
just to earn a little extra money for the family.

629
00:24:51,839 --> 00:24:53,240
Now Qiu'er

630
00:24:53,359 --> 00:24:55,920
is always working outside jobs, and wants to have a baby.

631
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:57,839
We old folks,

632
00:24:57,839 --> 00:24:59,920
should help out where we can.

633
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,319
Come on, come on, drink.

634
00:25:01,599 --> 00:25:02,960
Uncle Tong, you're seventy this year, right?

635
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,119
Sixty-nine.

636
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,880
Uncle Tong, let me ask you.

637
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:10,039
How many complete scripts can you still write?

638
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:14,519
Weiguo, let's not talk about this, let's eat.

639
00:25:14,519 --> 00:25:15,319
What if this story

640
00:25:15,319 --> 00:25:16,480
Eat more vegetables.

641
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:18,119
is the last script you ever write?

642
00:25:18,559 --> 00:25:19,480
Would you be content with that?

643
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,640
What are you saying?

644
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:24,039
Stop talking.

645
00:25:24,319 --> 00:25:25,279
Here, come on.

646
00:25:25,279 --> 00:25:26,400
Eat, eat your food.

647
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:27,599
Eat, eat.

648
00:25:27,599 --> 00:25:28,400
Uncle Tong,

649
00:25:29,279 --> 00:25:31,599
I still remember how much I admired you as a child.

650
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:33,680
I also really appreciated the things you wrote.

651
00:25:34,839 --> 00:25:35,680
Just eat, okay?

652
00:25:35,799 --> 00:25:38,000
You told me the story of *The Eagle Shooting Heroes*.

653
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,759
You said never to associate with

654
00:25:39,759 --> 00:25:41,720
people or things you look down upon.

655
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:44,960
You said to stick to your principles and ideals.

656
00:25:46,279 --> 00:25:47,279
But now...

657
00:25:47,359 --> 00:25:48,319
Think about it.

658
00:25:48,319 --> 00:25:49,559
Are you really content?

659
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:52,839
Can you swallow this indignity?

660
00:25:57,279 --> 00:25:58,759
I'm sorry, Grandpa Tong, Grandma Tong.

661
00:25:58,960 --> 00:25:59,799
Stop eating.

662
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:01,279
What are you doing?

663
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:08,160
You're the one with all the talk.

664
00:26:11,559 --> 00:26:12,480
What are you doing?

665
00:26:13,799 --> 00:26:15,640
I think you're only suited to eat this Japanese food.

666
00:26:16,079 --> 00:26:18,000
You're just like that "Solitary Gourmet."

667
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:18,799
Did I say something wrong just now?

668
00:26:18,799 --> 00:26:20,079
You didn't say anything wrong.

669
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,680
But can you speak properly?

670
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:25,160
You're harsh to me, Uncle Wang, Uncle Qiu, my cousin...

671
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,880
We can tolerate you being so mean to us.

672
00:26:27,759 --> 00:26:29,839
Grandpa Tong has written articles his whole life.

673
00:26:29,839 --> 00:26:31,119
In the end, to be criticized as worthless

674
00:26:31,119 --> 00:26:32,200
by some youngster,

675
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,680
and have to rely on connections to get by...

676
00:26:33,839 --> 00:26:35,400
Do you think he really feels good about that?

677
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,559
That's precisely why I need to advise him

678
00:26:36,559 --> 00:26:37,079
not to waste time

679
00:26:37,079 --> 00:26:38,559
on things not worth wasting it on.

680
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,440
He doesn't have that much time left to waste.

681
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,240
What are you laughing at?

682
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:46,640
You only seem smart.

683
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:48,599
Actually, you don't understand people's hearts at all.

684
00:26:48,599 --> 00:26:50,519
No, it's that you don't *want* to understand.

685
00:26:50,759 --> 00:26:51,759
Because in your eyes,

686
00:26:51,759 --> 00:26:53,359
there's only one standard way to live:

687
00:26:53,359 --> 00:26:55,160
your way, Martin's way.

688
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,160
As soon as anyone thinks differently from you,

689
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:58,240
you think they're wrong.

690
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,599
You think you're correcting them,

691
00:26:59,599 --> 00:27:00,680
but is that really helping them?

692
00:27:01,359 --> 00:27:03,400
Life really isn't as long as you imagine.

693
00:27:04,079 --> 00:27:06,039
I speak bluntly, it can hurt people.

694
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:08,480
That's because I don't have that much time to waste.

695
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,640
You're really narcissistic.

696
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,960
As if only your time is precious.

697
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,480
Pretending to be profound.

698
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:21,440
What are you looking at?

699
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:23,880
I know why you've been avoiding me since you came back.

700
00:27:24,359 --> 00:27:25,279
Rest assured,

701
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:27,000
I had no interest in you before,

702
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:28,640
and I have even less interest in you now.

703
00:27:29,079 --> 00:27:30,079
So you can just settle down

704
00:27:30,079 --> 00:27:32,279
and put your heart back in the Pacific Ocean.

705
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:47,160
Brother Tong, drink, drink.

706
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:50,279
Brother Tong, let me tell you.

707
00:27:51,279 --> 00:27:53,799
I'd rather have a hole in my stomach

708
00:27:54,279 --> 00:27:56,720
than let a crack form in our friendship.

709
00:27:57,079 --> 00:27:57,559
Right!

710
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:58,160
Drink!

711
00:27:58,279 --> 00:27:59,119
Well said!

712
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,079
Bro, bro, let me.

713
00:28:16,079 --> 00:28:17,559
I... I'll have one with you, bro.

714
00:28:18,599 --> 00:28:20,039
Come on, I... I'll toast you.

715
00:28:20,039 --> 00:28:21,359
Stop drinking, you've had enough.

716
00:28:21,359 --> 00:28:23,000
It's fine, bro, I can hold my liquor.

717
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,400
I'm from Qingdao.

718
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:25,880
I'm a really heavy drinker, bro.

719
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:27,799
Even if you're from Qingdao, you've had a lot.

720
00:28:27,799 --> 00:28:29,079
It's fine, bro.

721
00:28:31,279 --> 00:28:32,000
You...

722
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:35,920
Eat something, eat something.

723
00:28:36,119 --> 00:28:37,160
I'll take this away for you.

724
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,759
Bro, you're so handsome.

725
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,039
What's wrong?

726
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:53,200
I can't drink anymore.

727
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,720
If you can't drink, then don't.

728
00:28:55,839 --> 00:28:59,119
What about our task?

729
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:03,759
No more drinking, anyone! Stop drinking!

730
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,640
Stop drinking, stop drinking.

731
00:29:06,039 --> 00:29:07,480
Sit down and rest, quick, quick.

732
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:17,079
We're not doing this anymore.

733
00:29:17,319 --> 00:29:18,920
Deposits aren't solicited this way.

734
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,400
That's how I got through it.

735
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:21,759
Those few are still kids.

736
00:29:21,759 --> 00:29:24,039
You feel sorry for them, but who feels sorry for me?

737
00:29:24,039 --> 00:29:25,559
If you really drink someone into a bad state,

738
00:29:25,559 --> 00:29:26,720
how will you explain it to their parents?

739
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:27,680
I only care about the task.

740
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,319
Get the deposits you're supposed to get.

741
00:29:29,319 --> 00:29:30,240
Are you kidding me?

742
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:31,720
How much can kids bring in?

743
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:33,960
They can't drink and they can't complete the task.

744
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:35,839
Are you going to shoulder their task?

745
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,200
I'll shoulder it.

746
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:39,200
It's not like I'm shouldering it.

747
00:29:44,519 --> 00:29:45,960
Brother Ming, please, no need to see me out.

748
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:46,759
Don't bother seeing me off.

749
00:29:46,759 --> 00:29:48,279
Please reconsider the loan matter.

750
00:29:48,279 --> 00:29:49,720
Contact me again if you need anything.

751
00:29:51,359 --> 00:29:52,079
Weiguo.

752
00:29:52,079 --> 00:29:53,920
I need to see you about something now.

753
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:57,480
Second brother, what's up?

754
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:07,000
Didn't big brother disagree?

755
00:30:08,759 --> 00:30:10,880
That's because he hasn't seen the money yet.

756
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,519
Once I bring in the money,

757
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:13,559
how could he disagree?

758
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:16,519
Is it reliable?

759
00:30:16,759 --> 00:30:19,039
That's why I need you as insurance.

760
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:22,119
Me as insurance?

761
00:30:22,359 --> 00:30:23,039
Yes.

762
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:25,799
Big brother cares for you the most.

763
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:28,599
When the time comes, help me persuade big brother.

764
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:30,400
Are you setting me up?

765
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:32,359
Why does this sound so shady to me?

766
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,720
I'll give you five percent of the shares.

767
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,279
Once the money is in place,

768
00:30:37,279 --> 00:30:40,160
the company account will be opened at your bank too.

769
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:41,400
It'll count as your performance.

770
00:30:41,759 --> 00:30:42,720
Is that enough?

771
00:30:44,359 --> 00:30:45,160
Really?

772
00:30:48,279 --> 00:30:49,759
Oh, my second brother!

773
00:30:52,039 --> 00:30:53,960
You're truly a lifesaver, like Song Jiang.

774
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:55,480
You've helped me tremendously.

775
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:57,759
I was just about to ask Weiguo

776
00:30:57,759 --> 00:30:59,240
to deposit some money with me,

777
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:00,440
to boost my performance numbers.

778
00:31:01,079 --> 00:31:02,119
That money from our company,

779
00:31:02,119 --> 00:31:03,680
must be at least eight to ten million, right?

780
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:05,039
I need to ask you a favor.

781
00:31:05,039 --> 00:31:06,400
Can we not deposit it all at once?

782
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,319
Let's split it into eight or ten installments.

783
00:31:08,319 --> 00:31:09,240
That way it looks like I have

784
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,279
performance every month for a year.

785
00:31:11,599 --> 00:31:14,039
What, you're asking Ma Weiguo for a favor?

786
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:17,359
That was before.

787
00:31:17,799 --> 00:31:19,319
I've now turned over a new leaf.

788
00:31:21,519 --> 00:31:22,519
Turned over a new leaf?

789
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:27,240
Come on, come on, drive!

790
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:29,240
Where are we going?

791
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,119
Take me home.

792
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:32,519
You have the nerve.

793
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,200
And I'm supposed to take you home?

794
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:37,160
Get out, walk back yourself. I have things to do.

795
00:31:37,359 --> 00:31:38,279
What things?

796
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:41,079
Do I have to tell you my business?

797
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,160
You're messing with me.

798
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:47,680
Hurry up.

799
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:48,279
Alright.

800
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,200
Heartless.

801
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:03,119
There's nothing wrong with this project.

802
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:04,880
But the environment isn't good right now.

803
00:32:05,279 --> 00:32:06,519
And you,

804
00:32:06,519 --> 00:32:08,680
don't have much practical operational experience.

805
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,039
How about

806
00:32:10,039 --> 00:32:11,880
transferring this project directly to us?

807
00:32:13,519 --> 00:32:14,559
The way you put it...

808
00:32:15,039 --> 00:32:16,759
couldn't be more blunt.

809
00:32:17,759 --> 00:32:18,839
But it's correct.

810
00:32:19,319 --> 00:32:22,039
Li Lianbao really is insulated from good luck.

811
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:23,559
Clearly the protagonist,

812
00:32:23,799 --> 00:32:25,759
why does he live like a non-player character?

813
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:27,400
Trouble follows him every moment.

814
00:32:28,119 --> 00:32:30,319
Now big brother and Tong Qiu are dragged in too.

815
00:32:31,839 --> 00:32:33,799
Looks like it won't be long

816
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,680
before I have to step in to bail someone out.

817
00:32:37,079 --> 00:32:39,160
What was that saying before?

818
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:40,799
Ma Weiguo,

819
00:32:41,359 --> 00:32:43,559
you're really going to plague me for life.

820
00:32:43,799 --> 00:32:45,759
Yes, that's the one.

821
00:32:52,559 --> 00:32:55,240
I've switched careers to insurance now.

822
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:56,599
Don't look down on it.

823
00:32:56,599 --> 00:32:59,039
It's a very meaningful industry.

824
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:00,319
And furthermore,

825
00:33:00,319 --> 00:33:03,799
it's a benevolent act that benefits humanity.

826
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,319
You know?

827
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:06,880
Ever since I entered this field,

828
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:08,720
my life suddenly

829
00:33:10,359 --> 00:33:11,880
is no longer aimless.

830
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,279
Listen to me.

831
00:33:13,559 --> 00:33:15,000
Stop chasing after these

832
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,319
startups and investments.

833
00:33:17,319 --> 00:33:19,240
Hurry up and join us.

834
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:22,240
Join our warm, big family.

835
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:24,400
Old Li, you know me.

836
00:33:24,559 --> 00:33:26,279
I don't invest in entrepreneurs

837
00:33:26,279 --> 00:33:27,599
over thirty years old.

838
00:33:28,319 --> 00:33:29,480
Young people,

839
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,920
have plenty of room to grow.

840
00:33:31,079 --> 00:33:32,640
But at our age,

841
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:34,160
with a bit of money in hand,

842
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:36,319
just enjoy life, that's enough.

843
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,800
Old Fei, where are you?

844
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:10,679
Lianbao.

845
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:11,519
Sorry about this.

846
00:34:11,519 --> 00:34:12,400
I have a last-minute meeting today.

847
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:13,599
I can't make it to the meal.

848
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:15,119
Alright.

849
00:34:15,639 --> 00:34:16,639
You go ahead and take care of your business.

850
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:17,960
We'll get together another time.

851
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,119
Let's meet up another day then.

852
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:42,280
The hotel owner came to console me, saying

853
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:44,239
Such a large private room

854
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:46,440
hasn't been booked for a long time.

855
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:49,199
The owner is a good person.

856
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,000
But he's right.

857
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:54,519
Those were the good old days.

858
00:34:55,559 --> 00:34:57,159
This place was always bustling.

859
00:34:57,920 --> 00:35:00,280
Everyone would come over to toast me.

860
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:03,159
Glasses clinking back and forth,

861
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:06,039
every drink was a bond of friendship.

862
00:35:06,559 --> 00:35:08,679
I used to think that on these dinner tables,

863
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:11,239
being lively and happy

864
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:13,679
was just a natural, given thing.

865
00:35:14,679 --> 00:35:16,440
Only now do I understand

866
00:35:17,440 --> 00:35:19,079
that hosting a dinner party

867
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:20,639
is so difficult.

868
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:44,320
Lianbao.

869
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:46,440
To be honest with you,

870
00:35:47,159 --> 00:35:49,840
these people are all dogs.

871
00:35:53,880 --> 00:35:54,880
Bullshit.

872
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:01,239
They really came for you.

873
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:05,039
Yes.

874
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:06,880
I was the one who set this up for you.

875
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:07,480
Alright.

876
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:09,119
You've had too much today.

877
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:13,000
But you want to squeeze money from them.

878
00:36:13,679 --> 00:36:15,079
Have you ever thought,

879
00:36:15,519 --> 00:36:17,360
when you were at your lowest,

880
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:20,920
did any of these bastards lift a finger to help?

881
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:26,280
Lianbao, I'll be straight with you.

882
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:29,719
This gathering,

883
00:36:30,239 --> 00:36:32,119
I never really wanted to arrange it.

884
00:36:36,119 --> 00:36:37,679
I bet fifty million.

885
00:36:38,679 --> 00:36:39,719
Fifty million.

886
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,320
Two projects.

887
00:36:42,679 --> 00:36:43,960
Just two projects.

888
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:46,159
Lost it all.

889
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:48,519
Up to my neck in debt.

890
00:36:49,159 --> 00:36:50,280
I thought to myself,

891
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:53,079
I can't even afford to play anymore myself,

892
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:55,079
why should I bother with you?

893
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:57,360
But then I thought again,

894
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:59,079
what if?

895
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:00,920
What if you got some money

896
00:37:01,199 --> 00:37:02,559
and bounced back?

897
00:37:03,559 --> 00:37:04,679
Lianbao.

898
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,679
You're not like those bastards.

899
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:08,760
You're not like me either.

900
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:10,519
You can make it.

901
00:37:11,159 --> 00:37:12,000
I believe in you.

902
00:37:19,159 --> 00:37:19,920
Earlier...

903
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:24,480
You drank too fast today, take it easy.

904
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:25,440
I'm okay.

905
00:37:26,599 --> 00:37:28,199
So, shall we have a bit more?

906
00:37:28,639 --> 00:37:29,239
Alright.

907
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:30,800
That money...

908
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:32,519
Alright, alright, alright.

909
00:37:39,679 --> 00:37:41,280
Manager Li, the bill is settled.

910
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:43,599
Let's go.

911
00:37:43,840 --> 00:37:44,480
What about them?

912
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:47,760
I'm tired.

913
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:27,639
Brother Liu.

914
00:38:28,239 --> 00:38:30,079
Sorry to bother you so late.

915
00:38:30,639 --> 00:38:32,719
My gout is acting up.

916
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,599
I have another engagement tomorrow noon,

917
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,639
driving will probably be tough.

918
00:38:36,639 --> 00:38:38,000
You'll have to come pick me up.

919
00:38:40,039 --> 00:38:41,400
No problem, no problem.

920
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:43,039
Get some rest, I'm hanging up.

921
00:39:26,079 --> 00:39:27,159
Hello, honey?

922
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:28,320
Wife.

923
00:39:28,719 --> 00:39:31,280
I've really run into an unexpected situation here.

924
00:39:31,599 --> 00:39:33,039
Can we postpone it for another couple of days?

925
00:39:33,079 --> 00:39:34,639
Then I'll come back to Beijing.

926
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,400
Don't trouble yourself with the trip.

927
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:37,719
I promise, as soon as I'm done here,

928
00:39:37,719 --> 00:39:39,360
I'll go to Xi'an immediately.

929
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:41,119
Okay, I have to go to a meeting now.

930
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,480
When will your money come through?

931
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:50,840
Is it reliable or not?

932
00:39:52,119 --> 00:39:53,679
If it really doesn't work, I'll ask Weiguo.

933
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:55,400
At least his money is readily available.

934
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:57,480
Go on, all of you go find Ma Weiguo!

935
00:39:57,480 --> 00:39:58,159
Without Ma Weiguo,

936
00:39:58,159 --> 00:39:59,559
you all can't survive, is that it?

937
00:40:01,079 --> 00:40:01,920
Honestly.

938
00:40:03,079 --> 00:40:05,280
Manager Li, who else are we meeting today?

939
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:11,840
Let's go, we're going to see Dong Qian.

940
00:40:12,159 --> 00:40:12,760
Got it.

941
00:40:17,519 --> 00:40:20,280
Li Lianbao, you're utterly shameless!

942
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:23,960
You just modified my project and used it.

943
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:25,119
Do you have any shame left?

944
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:27,559
This circle is only so big.

945
00:40:27,559 --> 00:40:29,119
Did you really think I wouldn't find out?

946
00:40:29,239 --> 00:40:31,000
I wasn't afraid of you knowing in the first place.

947
00:40:31,559 --> 00:40:33,400
Besides, everyone wants a good project.

948
00:40:34,039 --> 00:40:35,119
Fair competition, then.

949
00:40:35,119 --> 00:40:35,840
Fair competition?

950
00:40:35,840 --> 00:40:37,639
Why don't you go find your own project?

951
00:40:38,679 --> 00:40:40,840
Arguing over this shows a lack of vision.

952
00:40:41,079 --> 00:40:42,840
We're both doing this for the boss's good.

953
00:40:44,719 --> 00:40:47,920
Fine, today I'll show some big-picture thinking.

954
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:51,000
I won't argue with you about who's right or wrong.

955
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:54,480
So, having trouble finding money, huh?

956
00:40:54,679 --> 00:40:55,760
Who says?

957
00:40:56,199 --> 00:40:58,119
I have several potential clients already.

958
00:40:59,559 --> 00:41:01,360
I need to choose carefully,

959
00:41:02,119 --> 00:41:03,639
and then maybe set up something like

960
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:05,400
a last-place elimination or something.

961
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:10,400
Li Lianbao, oh Li Lianbao.

962
00:41:13,679 --> 00:41:17,239
We've known each other since we were born, right?

963
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:19,079
We know each other inside out.

964
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:20,639
Why are you putting on an act with me?

965
00:41:21,719 --> 00:41:23,639
Yes, usually

966
00:41:23,639 --> 00:41:25,559
we always bicker as soon as we meet.

967
00:41:25,639 --> 00:41:26,840
But when it comes down to it,

968
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:28,679
there's no deep-seated hatred, right?

969
00:41:29,039 --> 00:41:31,559
Our mothers are sworn sisters.

970
00:41:31,559 --> 00:41:32,840
My grandma and your grandpa...

971
00:41:32,840 --> 00:41:33,800
Stop, stop, stop.

972
00:41:34,119 --> 00:41:35,840
Let's not trace it back any further.

973
00:41:36,199 --> 00:41:37,400
If we keep going back like this,

974
00:41:37,559 --> 00:41:39,679
we'll really become childhood sweethearts!

975
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,159
You know,

976
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:43,639
sometimes I don't know

977
00:41:43,639 --> 00:41:45,320
if you're really naive or just pretending.

978
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:48,840
What do you mean?

979
00:41:50,599 --> 00:41:51,880
Usually,

980
00:41:52,119 --> 00:41:54,000
I really wish I could step on you a couple of times.

981
00:41:54,440 --> 00:41:56,480
But when I see you at your wit's end,

982
00:41:56,599 --> 00:41:58,119
I hope you can pull through.

983
00:41:58,880 --> 00:42:00,960
Just look at society today.

984
00:42:01,320 --> 00:42:04,239
Those who can truly let their guard down and be honest

985
00:42:04,239 --> 00:42:06,760
seem to be only a few of us

986
00:42:06,760 --> 00:42:08,239
who grew up together.

987
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:14,960
So, you, towards me...
